Everett Eissenstat has been appointed as Deputy Assistant to the President for International Economic Affairs and Deputy Director of the National Economic Council. He will also serve as the President's representative and lead negotiator for international summits that address economic affairs. Eissenstat has extensive experience in trade issues, having previously served as Chief International Trade Counsel to the U.S. Senate Finance Committee and Assistant U.S. Trade Representative for the Americas. He will play a critical role in advancing policies that promote job creation and economic growth. Eissenstat holds a J.D. cum laude from the University of Oklahoma, an M.A. in Latin American Studies from the University of Texas, and a B.S. in Political Science and Spanish from Oklahoma State University.